					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Eventually you have to realize that everything is numbers when it comes to assembly programming. Sometimes these numbers are values and sometimes they're addresses.<br /><br />When programming 6502 assembly you end up using pointers a lot if you don't want to replicate code. An index indicates a pointer, which points to another index and so on. It happens a lot in games, where you have several types of data to work with (metatiles, level maps, music patterns, sprite definitions, etc.).</div>

